The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal govt to honour medallists 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Bengal govt to honour medallists 
            BRIEFS                
	Calcutta: The West Bengal government will felicitate the 10 Commonwealth Games medallists from the state and award them with Rs 5 lakh for gold, Rs 3 lakh for silver and Rs 2 lakh for bronze medal winners.         
	This was announced by the state sports minister Kanti Ganguly, on Wednesday. Though the date has not been finalised, the event will be held before November 14, said Ganguly.   
	Ticket protest  
	New Delhi: Angry ticket seekers, on Wednesday, protested against organsing committee (OC), forcing authorities to strengthen security arrangements at the OC headquarters.   
	Marathon  
	New Delhi: Watching the Games marathon will be easy, on Thursday, with Delhi police easing security restrictions for the event and allowing spectators at eight spots, after facing flak for overzealous measures during cycling event which drove the people away.   
	Wada unhappy  
	New Delhi: The World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada) has expressed its displeasure to the Games OC over the manner in which dope testing is being carried out. According to sources, international standards of dope testing have not fully been followed in the Games.         
